": "Antonín Dvorák", "w": "8715"}, {"t": "Cotton Tail", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "30186"}, {"t": "Trees", "c": "Oscar Rasbach", "w": "25556"}, {"t": "Tootin' Through the Roof", "c": "Duke Ellington", "w": "31179"}]}, {"id": "33124", "date": "1974-11-08", "label": "New York Jazz Repertory Company: The Music of Louis Armstrong", "venue": "Main Hall", "roles": ["trumpet"], "works": [{"t": "Selections (unspecified)", "c": null, "w": "104450"}]}], "works_created": [], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Konitz Lee", "relation": "played with", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I had decided that I just wanted to get to play duets with people and I called different people, unlikely people, like Ray Nance... at the record date, I went “da da” and he went to the next movement.", "doc_title": "Konitz Lee — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/Konitz-Lee-Transcription-2020.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Terry Clark", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "What about the – what did – what was your – what is your learning that came from sitting in the trumpet section with Cat Anderson, Shorty Baker, Ray Nance, and others in the Ellington band?", "doc_title": "Terry Clark — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://amhistory.si.edu/jazz/Terry-Clark/Clark_Terry_Transcript.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Horace Henderson", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "And I had a great band there. This is when I had Walter Fuller, trumpet, Ray Nance, and I had a little guy from Ohio named PeeWee Jackson, Harry Jackson.", "doc_title": "68514_Horace Henderson oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/68514/"}, {"speaker": "Quentin Jackson", "relation": "in music group with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "Well, the trumpets was Al Killian, Shelton Hemphill, Francis Williams, Shorty Baker, and Ray Nance.", "doc_title": "61539_Butter Jackson oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/61539/"}, {"speaker": "Loren Schoenberg", "relation": "has met", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "So I interviewed Hymie Shertzer and then I interviewed Ray Nance when I was about 15 or so.", "doc_title": "Loren Schoenberg interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, January 14, 2019", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/loren-schoenberg-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-january-14-2019"}, {"speaker": "Trummy Young", "relation": "friend of", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "I dug Budd, and I dug Ray Nance, and Walter Fuller and I were good friends.", "doc_title": "52300_Trummy Young oral history interview", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/52300/"}]}